gov.usgs.volcanoes.core.legacy.ew.message

Class TraceBuf

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.volcanoes.core.legacy.ew.message.Message
      • gov.usgs.volcanoes.core.legacy.ew.message.TraceBuf

  • public class TraceBuf
extends Message
    A Java implementation of the TYPE_TRACEBUF and TYPE_TRACEBUF2 earthworm messages. startTime and endTime are stored in their native format: decimal seconds since Jan 1. 1970.

    The data fields in this class were derived from trace_buf.h in the earthworm source.
    TODO: better separate TRACEBUF from TRACEBUF2
    Author:
    Dan Cervelli

      • processBytes

        public void processBytes(DataInputStream in,
                boolean isTraceBuf2)
                  throws IOException
        Fills the fields based on raw message data. There is a flag to specify whether this is a TRACEBUF or a TRACEBUF2. In theory, this could be avoided if the version field in TRACEBUF2 was checked but there are some issues with this, so I leave it to the user to choose.
        Parameters:
        in - the input stream
        isTraceBuf2 - whether this is a TRACEBUF2
        Throws:
        IOException

      • register

        public void register()
        Registers the starting time to the nearest even interval based on the wave's sampling rate. The offset between the original start time and the registered time is stored in registrationOffset.

      • traceBufToWave

        public static Wave traceBufToWave(List<TraceBuf> traceBufs)
        Converts a list of time-ordered, non-overlapping TraceBufs into a Wave. Skips tracebufs whose sampling rate does not match the first tracebuf. Starting time will be rounded to the nearest even interval based on the wave's sampling rate. Work with timestamps as microseconds to avoid rounding errors.
        Parameters:
        traceBufs - the TraceBufs (must be sorted in time order)
        Returns:
        the wave
